        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 1:22PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 121 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Halls Mills, or near Mc Grady. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hays...
Mulberry...
Abshers...
Dockery...
and Fairplains.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
